Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on robotic reinforcement learning and proposes a novel empirical analysis to evaluate the difficulty of Reacher tasks in robotic manipulation. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses Deep Reinforcement Learning and Deep Deterministic Policy Gradients, which are machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the application of AI techniques to robotic control. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - Although not the main focus, the paper mentions the use of vision-based sensors in robotic manipulation. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the control of unmodeled systems using reinforcement learning, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
